# 62b24685159b4110bc898fb6f8f9307c
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpHdrCopy.en.rst:37
msgid ""
":c:func:`TSHttpHdrCopy` works correctly even if :arg:`src_bufp` and "
":arg:`dest_bufp` point to different :ref:`developer-plugins-marshal-"
"buffers`. Make sure that you create the destination HTTP header before "
"copying into it."
msgstr ""

# a317338994774414a58f455d6d0d93be
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpHdrCopy.en.rst:43
msgid ""
":c:func:`TSHttpHdrCopy` appends the port number to the domain of the URL "
"portion of the header. For example, a copy of http://www.example.com "
"appears as http://www.example.com:80 in the destination buffer."
msgstr ""

